43:50.714 --> 43:52.216
Beaumont will never forget it.

43:52.299 --> 43:54.801
I will never forget it.

44:00.516 --> 44:01.600
Final answer?

44:20.285 --> 44:21.745
Fuck it. Let's do it.

44:22.454 --> 44:23.455
Yes!

44:23.539 --> 44:24.540
My man.

44:24.623 --> 44:26.333
That's a good call, Jimmy. Smart.

44:26.875 --> 44:30.921
I gotta treat you
like a scumbag again, man. Sorry.

44:35.926 --> 44:37.386
All right, let's go.

44:43.475 --> 44:45.060
How'd he strike you?

44:45.561 --> 44:48.480
He didn't fill me
with an overwhelming sense of confidence.

44:49.731 --> 44:53.235
Well, that will be moot in about an hour.

44:54.903 --> 44:58.073
At trial,
Mr. Hall's entire theory of defense

44:58.156 --> 45:00.117
boiled down to a simple proposition.

45:00.701 --> 45:04.413
Due to a personality disorder
that makes him susceptible to suggestion

45:04.496 --> 45:06.874
and pathologically eager to please,

45:06.957 --> 45:10.961
